e explanatory notes and the story of the composition and reception of each essay. The volume opens with a full listing of all Stevenson’s essays followed by a substantial introductory discussion of Stevenson’s career as essayist, the characteristics and literary contexts of his essays, and the critical and popular reception of his essays from the 1870s to the present day. The volume Introduction proper then presents the publication history of Virginibus Puerisque, the reception of the book and notable characteristics of the collection taken as a whole: its style and shape, and the aesthetic and ethical vision it presents.Key FeaturesProvides an introductory overview of Stevenson as essayistIncludes composition and publication history of each essayProvides a publication history of the volume of collected essaysIncludes notes identifying literary references, Stevenson’s idiosyncratic diction, social and historical allusions and cross references to Stevenson’s other works  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh1 aAbrahamson, Robert-Louis, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311078043740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978074864385140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748643851423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748643851/original  a978-3-11-078043-7  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK